  <section class="about-bio">
    <p>I'm Blake Beyel. I serve as Corporate Counsel for Beyel Brothers Inc., a heavy equipment rental and crane services company based in Cocoa, Florida. My work sits squarely on the hinge between legal and business: contracts, compliance, risk, vendor review, and the operational plumbing that makes a company actually run.</p>
    <p>I came to law through a financial-analysis background. I hold an MBA and an MS in Accounting &amp; Financial Forensics from Florida Tech, earned my JD from Barry University School of Law in 2024, and was admitted to the Florida Bar that same year. My law school research included a paper critiquing UCC Article 12 and its approach to decentralized virtual currencies.</p>
    <p>Legal Overflow is where I work out loud about what AI tools are and are not doing inside in-house practice. I write a weekly article, a dispatch, and the running Case Log, covering <strong>both</strong> the legal practice and the business functions the practice exists to serve.</p>
    <p>There are no sponsors and no advertisers on this site. I use AI tools to draft. It would be hypocritical not to, given what this site covers. Every article is reviewed, revised, and signed off by me before it goes live. The tools I cover are tools I use; when I get something wrong, I publish a correction on the same page.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-facts about-facts-2">
    <div class="about-fact"><div class="f-n">63</div><div class="f-l">Articles published</div></div>
    <div class="about-fact"><div class="f-n">2024</div><div class="f-l">Florida Bar admitted</div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-bio">
    <h2 style="font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 400; font-size: 42px; letter-spacing: -.01em; margin: 0 0 20px;">Editorial standards</h2>
    <p>I interview on background where needed and on the record where possible. Names of specific firms, matters, and counsel are changed or omitted when a source requests it. I do not accept gifts, equity, or affiliate revenue from any company whose products I write about.</p>
    <p>If you believe something I've published is wrong, write to <a href="mailto:corrections@legaloverflow.com" style="color: var(--accent-deep); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);">blake@beyelbrothers.com</a>. I take these seriously and publish in-line updates with a visible diff.</p>
  </section>
